{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012dgoWArvPbhek8k99jXAkg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `elasticsearch-headless` is failing DNS resolution. This is happening because the StatefulSet is using `elasticsearch-0.elasticsearch-headless` as the subdomain, but the headless service needs to be in the same namespace. \n\nIn Kubernetes, for a headless service to work with StatefulSets, the DNS is typically:\n- `<pod-name>.<service-name>.<namespace>.svc.cluster.local`\n\nBut when you query just `elasticsearch-headless` from within the pod, it should resolve to the service's endpoints. The issue might be that:\n1. The pod is only partially ready, so it's not yet included as an endpoint\n2. The DNS lookup for `elasticsearch-headless` is failing, possibly because the service itself wasn't created or the DNS search paths aren't configured correctly in the pod.\n\nActually, this DNS error might just be a transient startup issue. I should look at the full logs more carefully to see if there are other problems, particularly around TLS or authentication that might be preventing the cluster from forming.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":912,"cache_read_input_tokens":39916,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":912},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b46e79cf-3f07-46ac-a7cf-24c58627c257","uuid":"bf7015d5-7953-4b5c-9283-9fa1a96c920d","request_id":"req_011CcLydpGB6ZLYbMVoMMdsR"}
