{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BE9X8W9drbLSFtnKT5GjaP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was deployed and the two issues that were fixed along the way:\n\n---\n\n**Deployed resources:**\n\n| Resource | Name | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| ConfigMap | `elasticsearch-config` | `elasticsearch.yml` with TLS + security settings |\n| Service (headless) | `elasticsearch-headless` | Pod-to-pod transport discovery on 9300/9200 |\n| Service (ClusterIP) | `es-http` | HTTPS access at port 9200 |\n| PodDisruptionBudget | `elasticsearch-pdb` | `minAvailable: 2` |\n| StatefulSet | `elasticsearch` | 3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` |\n\n**Two issues fixed mid-deployment:**\n\n1. **`publishNotReadyAddresses: true`** on the headless Service — without this, Kubernetes omits not-ready pods from DNS, so nodes couldn't discover each other via `elasticsearch-headless` until at least one was already healthy (a DNS bootstrapping deadlock).\n\n2. **`podManagementPolicy: Parallel`** on the StatefulSet — the default `OrderedReady` only creates the next pod once the previous is Ready, but ES needs a 2/3 quorum to elect a master before any node becomes Ready. All 3 must start simultaneously.\n\n**Final state:** Cluster is `green`, 3/3 nodes joined, master on `elasticsearch-2`, reads and writes succeed over HTTPS through `es-http:9200`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":520,"cache_read_input_tokens":51204,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":520},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b46e79cf-3f07-46ac-a7cf-24c58627c257","uuid":"144dc33f-313d-4834-b9c7-dd9281839fa4","request_id":"req_011CcLzC9WhT6V2HCRkdFxtM"}
